## Rule 1 — No Hardcoded Strings
- Move all hardcoded strings to `lib/core/constants/app_strings.dart`
- Use static const fields. Example: static const String loginTitle = 'Welcome Back';
- Reference in UI as: Text(AppStrings.loginTitle)

## Rule 2 — No Hardcoded Colors
- Move all hardcoded colors to `lib/core/constants/app_colors.dart`
- Use static const fields. Example: static const Color primary = Color(0xFF1A73E8);
- Reference in UI as: color: AppColors.primary
- Never use Colors.red, Colors.blue, or Color(0xFF...) directly in widget files

## Rule 3 — MVVM Pattern
- Each feature has two files:
  - `<feature>_screen.dart` → UI only (widget tree, layout, no logic)
  - `<feature>_view_model.dart` → all logic, state, API calls (extends ChangeNotifier)
- Never put business logic inside screen files
- Never put widgets inside ViewModel files
- Screen listens to ViewModel via Provider or Riverpod

## Rule 4 — Test Coverage
- Every ViewModel must have a corresponding test file in `test/` folder
- Test file named: `<feature>_view_model_test.dart`
- Cover all public methods, state changes, and edge cases
- Widget tests required for every screen file
- Minimum coverage target: 80%
